data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
This form allows you to move a computer in and out of the OU for resolving issues with connecting users to Eduroam after the 10/27/2015 cutover from LeopardSecure.
Enter in the computer name, and click "Move to OU for fix". Wait a couple of minutes, and then run "gpupdate /force". And then run "netsh wlan show profile".
Netsh should now show "eduroam" under "User profiles" -- NOT under "Group Policy Profiles". If not, continue to run "gpupdate /force" until such time as the "eduroam" profile shows under "User Profiles"
Fix the issue with eduroam by manually connecting to the network with the full email address.
Once the issue is fixed and the user is successfully connected to eduroam, click the "Move back AFTER fix" button -- and repeat the steps with "gpupdate /force" until the netsh command shows the profile back under "Group Policy Profiles".
After this, you MAY have to re-connect the user to eduroam.
